Excellent! We now have a well-rounded set of outcome measures for our clinical trial:

* Primary endpoint: Change in corneal endothelial cell density at Day 28 after phacoemulsification cataract surgery
	+ Measured using non-contact specular microscopy;
	+ Paired t-test to compare mean percentage change from baseline of FIDIAL PLUS to mean percentage change of IAL®-F at Day 28.
* Secondary endpoint:
	+ Incidence of a significant rise in intraocular pressure (≥30 mmHg) during the investigation;
	+ McNemar's test to compare the proportion of eyes with a significant rise in IOP to the proportion of eyes without such a rise;
	+ Measured using a Goldmann tonometer.
	+ Time frame: Up to 28 days.
* Secondary endpoint:
	+ Incidence of ocular Treatment Emergent Adverse Events (TEAEs);
	+ Recorded using standardized terminology (MedDRA);
	+ Categorized by System Organ Class (SOC) and Preferred Term (PT).
	+ Time frame: Up to 28 days.
	+ Serious TEAEs will be defined as adverse events that led to death, serious deterioration in health, permanent impairment, hospitalization, or medical/surgical intervention to prevent life-threatening illness or injury.

We will use appropriate data analysis methods to evaluate the significance and inter-group differences of each outcome measure. We are now well on our way to designing a comprehensive and relevant outcome measures plan for our clinical trial.

